Abdulkadir Jeli Abubakar III, the Sokoto State Commissioner of Home Affairs, is dead, The PUNCH reports.  He died on Thursday evening, after a protracted illness. The late Abubakar, a younger brother to Sultan Muhammadu Sa’ad Abubakar, was a former commissioner for information, during Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal’s first tenure. Details of his death are still sketchy, as there is no official statement from the Sokoto state government. The deceased, who was survived by two wives and many children, had been buried according to Islamic rites. Source Shehu Shagari’s body arrives Sokoto State on Saturday, December 29, 2018. The body of late former president Shehu Shagari has arrived at the Sultan Abubakar International Airport in Sokoto, his home state. The body left the nation’s capital, Abuja, earlier today for burial in Sokoto State. His body was received… December 29, 2018 In "Top Stories" By Muhammad Bello Sokoto -   Gov. Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto State has assigned portfolios to the 26 new commissioners and members of the State Executive Council swore-in on Friday. This is contained in a statement by Abubakar Shekara, Director General, Media and Public Affairs to the Sokoto State Governor… November 3, 2018 In "Politics" SOKOTO - The Permanent Secretary, Sokoto State Pilgrims Welfare Agency, Alhaji Salihu Gatawa, is dead. A statement signed by Abubakar Dangusau, Special Assistant, Press Affairs to Gov. Aliyu Wamako said Gatawa died in Kaduna on Sunday at the age of 51, after a brief illness. It said that the deceased… June 9, 2014 In "News"